{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tamasfe/taplo/pulls/211", "id": 840969438, "node_id": "PR_kwDOD9_g584yICze", "html_url": "https://github.com/tamasfe/taplo/pull/211", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tamasfe/taplo/pull/211.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tamasfe/taplo/pull/211.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tamasfe/taplo/issues/211", "number": 211, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "feat: Massive Refactor and Rewrite", "user": {"login": "tamasfe", "id": 25967296, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI1OTY3Mjk2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/25967296?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe", "html_url": "https://github.com/tamasfe", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "One of the reasons why I always kept postponing patches and updates in this project was the fact that it was pretty hard to maintain. When I originally wrote most of it, I barely had time and just wanted to get features out ASAP.\r\n\r\nThe [Even Better TOML](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=tamasfe.even-better-toml) has recently passed the 100K installs mark, I felt that some cleanup and care was long overdue.\r\n\r\nThis PR is pretty much a rewrite and/or a major refactor of Taplo with the only exception of the parser, which I would love to rewrite as well but I'm already pushing my time-limits.\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n- [x] Rewrite of the DOM, it now uses a reference-counted implementation where each node is cheap to clone and to juggle around.\r\n- [x] Rewrite of the CLI as well, it is now a first-class citizen not just something quickly thrown together.\r\n- [x] Integration of [jsonschema](https://github.com/Stranger6667/jsonschema-rs), most (all?) JSON Schema features are now supported and the limitations of the current implementation are non-existent.\r\n- [x] Support of [schema store](https://www.schemastore.org/json/) catalog and schemas\r\n- [x] The shared code between the CLI and the language server is now properly extracted into `taplo-common`, so the CLI and the LSP are no longer out of sync.\r\n- [x] The external environment is now abstracted away into a trait, so both the LSP and the CLI should run pretty much anywhere with minimal plumbing\r\n- [x] [tracing](https://github.com/tokio-rs/tracing) is used for all logging\r\n- [x] Refactor and workspace support in the LSP\r\n- [x] All [toml-test](https://github.com/BurntSushi/toml-test) tests now pass\r\n- [x] Proper benchmarks via criterion (the new DOM is slightly slower initially due to allocations, but not too much)\r\n- [x] Completions and hover in the LSP (the building blocks are there, but the cursor queries require some plumbing)\r\n- [ ] The LSP is part of the CLI as well, and the VSCode extension works with it, WASM bindings are yet to be reimplemented\r\n- [x] Flexible configuration options in the LSP\r\n- [x] Proper directives in TOML files (e.g. schema)\r\n\r\n## Breaking Changes\r\n\r\nProbably a lot, but here are a few notable ones:\r\n\r\n- The DOM API is completely different, although migration should be rather easy.\r\n- Chrono feature has been removed, it can be reintroduced later though if needed.\r\n- As with the DOM layout, error types have also changed.\r\n- Date types are now separate syntax-kinds.\r\n- Even though we had no MSRV policy, I clearly used 1.58 features during the rewrite\r\n- The Even Better Toml vscode extension also gets a facelift with some configuration options changed\r\n\r\nMerging this PR should:\r\n\r\n- close #3 \r\n- close #205\r\n- close #197\r\n- close #196\r\n- close #185\r\n- close #181\r\n- close #179\r\n- close #176\r\n- close #174 \r\n- close #172\r\n- close #167\r\n- close #123\r\n- close #136\r\n- close #121\r\n- close #120\r\n- close #97\r\n- close #57", "created_at": "2022-02-06T00:58:15Z", "updated_at": "2022-03-26T22:20:06Z", "closed_at": "2022-03-26T22:19:52Z", "merged_at": "2022-03-26T22:19:49Z", "merge_commit_sha": "a3f6664efbb6f66d42a3e6470033040728851412", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tamasfe/taplo/pulls/211/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tamasfe/taplo/pulls/211/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tamasfe/taplo/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tamasfe/taplo/issues/211/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tamasfe/taplo/statuses/8cbaa97b8ddd088a544b892790fef490d03ef3f9", "head": {"label": "tamasfe:next", "ref": "next", "sha": "8cbaa97b8ddd088a544b892790fef490d03ef3f9", "user": {"login": "tamasfe", "id": 25967296, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI1OTY3Mjk2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/25967296?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe", "html_url": "https://github.com/tamasfe", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tamasfe/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tama